14 FC Barcelona season|2013\u201314]]\n|5||1||6||1||1<ref group=\"lower-alpha\" name=\"UCL\"/>||0||0||0||12||2\n|-\n!colspan=\"2\"|Total\n!392!!12!!58!!4!!131!!2!!12!!0!!593!!18\n|-\n!colspan=\"3\"|Career totals\n!481!!18!!58!!4!!131!!2!!12!!0!!682!!24\n|}\n;Notes\n{{Reflist|group=lower-alpha}}\n\n===International===\n:Source:<ref name=\"RSSSF\"/>\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|colspan=\"3\"|[[Spain national football team|Spain]]\n|-\n!Year!!Apps!!Goals\n|-\n|2000||1||0\n|-\n|2001||4||0\n|-\n|2002||10||1\n|-\n|2003||8||0\n|-\n|2004||10||0\n|-\n|2005||10||0\n|-\n|2006||10||0\n|-\n|2007||5||0\n|-\n|2008||14||1\n|-\n|2009||8||0\n|-\n|2010||14||1\n|-\n|2011||4||0\n|-\n|2012||1||0\n|-\n|2013||1||0\n|-\n!Total!!100!!3\n|}\n\n===International goals===\n:Source:<ref name=\"RSSSF\"/>\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n! # !! Date !! Venue !! Opponent !! Score !! Result !! Competition\n|-\n| 1. || 17 April 2002 || [[Windsor Park]], [[Belfast]], [[Northern Ireland]] || {{fb|NIR}} || 0\u2013'''4''' || 0\u20135 || [[Exhibition game|Friendly]]\n|-\n| 2. || 11 October 2008 || [[A. Le Coq Arena]], [[Tallinn]], [[Estonia]] || {{fb|EST}} || 0\u2013'''3''' || 0\u20133 || [[2010 FIFA World Cup qualification \u2013 UEFA Group 5|2010 World Cup qualification]]\n|-\n| 3. || 7 July 2010 || [[Moses Mabhida Stadium|Moses Mabhida]], [[Durban]], [[South Africa]] || {{fb|GER}} || 0\u2013'''1''' || 0\u20131 || [[2010 FIFA World Cup knockout stage#Germany vs Spain|2010 FIFA World Cup]]\n|}\n\n==Honours==\n\n===Club===\n'''Barcelona'''<ref name=\"SW\">{{cite web|url=https://int.soccerway.com/players/carles-puyol-saforcada/325/|title=Puyol \u2013 Trophies|publisher=Soccerway|accessdate=2 December 2015}}</ref>\n*[[La Liga]]: [[2004\u201305 La Liga|2004\u201305]], [[2005\u201306 La Liga|2005\u201306]], [[2008\u201309 La Liga|2008\u201309]], [[2009\u201310 La Liga|2009\u201310]], [[2010\u201311 La Liga|2010\u201311]], [[2012\u201313 La Liga|2012\u201313]]\n*[[Copa del Rey]]: [[2008\u201309 Copa del Rey|2008\u201309]], [[2011\u201312 Copa del Rey|2011\u201312]]\n*[[Supercopa de Espa\u00f1a]]: [[2005 Supercopa de Espa\u00f1a|2005]], [[2006 Supercopa de Espa\u00f1a|2006]], [[2009 Supercopa de Espa\u00f1a|2009]], [[2010 Supercopa de Espa\u00f1a|2010]]\n*[[UEFA Champions League]]: [[2005\u201306 UEFA Champions League|2005\u201306]], [[2008\u201309 UEFA Champions League|2008\u201309]], [[2010\u201311 UEFA Champions League|2010\u201311]]\n*[[UEFA Super Cup]]: [[2009 UEFA Super Cup|2009]]\n*[[FIFA Club World Cup]]: [[2009 FIFA Club World Cup|2009]], [[2011 FIFA Club World Cup|2011]]\n\n===International===\n[[File:Germany and Argentina face off in the final of the World Cup 2014 -2014-07-13 (13).jpg|thumb|Puyol at the [[2014 FIFA World Cup Final]], alongside [[Gisele B\u00fcndchen]]]]\n*[[FIFA World Cup]]: [[2010 FIFA World Cup|2010]]<ref name=\"SW\"/>\n*[[UEFA European Championship]]: [[UEFA Euro 2008|2008]]<ref name=\"SW\"/>\n*[[Summer Olympic Games|Summer Olympics]]: [[Silver medal]] [[Football at the 2000 Summer Olympics|2000]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://arxiu.fcbarcelona.cat/web/english/futbol/temporada_10-11/plantilla/jugadors/puyol.html|title=Carles Puyol Saforcada|publisher=FC Barcelona|accessdate=2 December 2015}}</ref>\n*[[FIFA Confederations Cup]]: Third-place [[2009 FIFA Confederations Cup|2009]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.cbc.ca/sports/soccer/spain-wins-wild-bronze-medal-match-1.858779|title=Spain wins wild bronze medal match|publisher=[[Canadian Broadcasting Corporation]]|date=28 June 2009|accessdate=2 December 2015}}</ref>\n\n===Individual===\n*[[Don Bal\u00f3n Award|La Liga Breakthrough Player of the Year]]: 2001\n*[[European Sports Magazines|ESM Team of the Year]]: [[European Sports Magazines#2001\u201302|2001\u201302]], [[European Sports Magazines#2002\u201303|2002\u201303]], [[European Sports Magazines#2004\u201305|2004\u201305]], [[European Sports Magazines#2005\u201306|2005\u201306]]\n*[[UEFA Team of the Year]]: [[UEFA Team of the Year#Team of the Year 2002|2002]], [[UEFA Team of the Year#Team of the Year 2005|2005]], [[UEFA Team of the Year#Team of the Year 2006|2006]], [[UEFA Team of the Year#Team of the Year 2008|2008]], [[UEFA Team of the Year#Team of the Year 2009|2009]], [[UEFA Team of the Year#Team of the Year 2010|2010]]\n*[[UEFA Club Football Awards#Best Defender|UEFA Club Best Defender]]: 2006<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.uefa.com/insideuefa/news/newsid=1498485.html|title=UEFA Club Defender of the Year|publisher=UEFA|date=1 May 2011|accessdate=1 February 2019}}</ref>\n*[[FIFPro#FIFA FIFPro World XI|FIFA/FIFPro World XI]]: 2007, 2008, [[2010 FIFA Ballon d'Or#FIFA/FIFPro World XI|2010]]\n*[[UEFA Euro 2008#Awards|UEFA Euro 2008 Team of the Tournament]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://en.euro2008.uefa.com/news/kind=1/newsid=729372.html#spain+dominate+team+tournament|title=Spain dominate Team of the Tournament|publisher=UEFA|date=30 June 2008|accessdate=30 June 2008|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080831080414/http://en.euro2008.uefa.com/news/kind%3D1/newsid%3D729372.html#spain+dominate+team+tournament|archivedate=31 August 2008}}</ref>\n*[[2009 FIFA Confederations Cup#Awards|2009 FIFA Confederations Cup Team of the Tournament]]\n*[[FIFA World Cup awards#All-Star Team|FIFA World Cup Dream Team]]: [[2010 FIFA World Cup|2010]]\n*[[LFP Awards#2011\u201312 Season|BBVA Fair Play award]]: 2011\u201312\n*[[UEFA Team of the Year#UEFA Ultimate Team of the Year|UEFA Ultimate Team of the Year]] (published 2015)<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.uefa.com/uefachampionsleague/news/newsid=2201679.html|title=Ultimate Team of the Year: The All-Time XI|publisher=UEFA|date=22 November 2015|accessdate=25 November 2015}}</ref>\n*World XI: Team of the 21st Century<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.givemesport.com/343841-world-xi-team-of-the-21st-century|title=World XI: Team of the 21st Century|publisher=Give Me Sport|date=2013|accessdate=20 January 2016}}</ref>\n*[[UEFA European Championship Teams